BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Orr0buJd_IBEZwPhXYNpC
SUMMARY:Songwriter Showcase w/Kristin Chambers\\\, Karen Laura Peters\\\, A
	llison Preisinger\\\, Fae Wiedenhoeft
DTSTAMP:20260325T021327Z
DTSTART:20260328T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:SFS presents an evening of music from 4 accomplished local song
	writers! \\nKristin Chambers’ warm\\\, soulful style blends jazz\\\, pop\\
	\, and folk influences into a captivating sound. With a background in clas
	sical voice and a natural talent for crafting compelling narratives\\\, he
	r music has found its way to stages and screens\\\, with placements on sho
	ws like “Better Call Saul\\\,” “The Young and the Restless\\\,” and “Love 
	is Blind.” Her latest release\\\, “Kristin Chambers Select Songs Vol. 1\\\
	,” is a curated journey through her musical evolution as a songwriter thus
	 far. \\nKaren Laura Peters is a singing cellist with a collaborative natu
	re and a gift for sharing her heart. While training at Oberlin Conservator
	y\\\, she fell in love with folk music and began writing her own songs\\\,
	 joining a band (Her Treehouse) that was featured in NPR’s All Songs Consi
	dered blog in 2019. Peters is presently a member of the indie-soul band Qu
	een of Hearts and co-founder of Momentum\\\, an organization that helps mu
	sicians feel inspired\\\, connected\\\, and empowered on their music journ
	ey. \\nAllison Preisinger is a Berklee College of Music graduate known for
	 evocative\\\, Americana-infused sounds and unique collaborations like her
	 recent work on a project with the National Park Service. 2025 saw the rel
	ease of her fourth album\\\, “Standing Steady\\\,” blending original music
	 with poetry from a number of sources. A multi-instrumentalist with a pass
	ion for connection\\\, Preisinger uses art to uplift and share the beauty 
	and complexity of human experience. \\nFae Wiedenhoeft is an award-winning
	 songwriter and classically trained vocalist who was hired to play Celtic 
	music in Canada at age 23 and has been a professional musician ever since.
	 She tours regularly and has played in 10 countries solo and with her band
	\\\, SeaStar. Wiedenhoeft has recorded over two dozen albums and teaches v
	oice\\\, guitar\\\, ukulele\\\, and songwriting. SeaStar’s latest album\\\
	, released in 2025\\\, is called “The In Between.” \\nDoors open at 7 pm f
	or the 7:30 pm concert in the Phinney Center’s Community Hall (lower Brick
	 Building). \\nTickets are available in advance online\\\, in-person at pr
	ior SFS concerts\\\, or at the door.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/even
	t/songwriter-showcase-w-kristin-chambers-karen-laura-peters-allison-preisi
	nger-fae-wiedenhoeft/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/songwriter-showcase-w-kristin-chamb
	ers-karen-laura-peters-allison-preisinger-fae-wiedenhoeft/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
